WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.491 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.491 --> 00:00:06.958 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:06.958 --> 00:01:08.089 align:middle line:90%


00:01:08.089 --> 00:01:11.640 align:middle line:10%
>> In the Southern
Sahara, in Niger,

00:01:11.640 --> 00:01:14.310 align:middle line:10%
the rocks contain one of
the world's most spectacular

00:01:14.310 --> 00:01:18.720 align:middle line:10%
and amazing examples
of primitive rock art,

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:21.870 align:middle line:10%
a large and a small
giraffe, side by side.

00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:26.010 align:middle line:90%


00:01:26.010 --> 00:01:28.440 align:middle line:84%
Although they are
nearly life-sized,

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:32.734 align:middle line:84%
they are carved
in minute detail.

00:01:32.734 --> 00:01:38.190 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:38.190 --> 00:01:41.662 align:middle line:90%
[SHEEP BLEATING]

00:01:41.662 --> 00:01:50.590 align:middle line:90%


00:01:50.590 --> 00:01:54.360 align:middle line:84%
>> This region is occupied
by nomadic herdsmen.

00:01:54.360 --> 00:01:56.880 align:middle line:90%


00:01:56.880 --> 00:01:59.570 align:middle line:84%
They have lived on these
plains for thousands of years.

00:01:59.570 --> 00:02:02.440 align:middle line:90%


00:02:02.440 --> 00:02:05.430 align:middle line:84%
Over years of roaming
around these Dabous rocks,

00:02:05.430 --> 00:02:07.660 align:middle line:84%
they have left behind a
huge number of carvings.

00:02:07.660 --> 00:02:10.960 align:middle line:90%


00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:14.420 align:middle line:90%
Over 800 have been counted.

00:02:14.420 --> 00:02:17.075 align:middle line:84%
Over 700 of which
represent animals.

00:02:17.075 --> 00:02:20.580 align:middle line:90%


00:02:20.580 --> 00:02:23.860 align:middle line:84%
Some show cattle,
but there are also

00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:29.080 align:middle line:84%
carvings of some of the wild
beasts that once lived here--

00:02:29.080 --> 00:02:38.355 align:middle line:90%
ostriches, gazelles, giraffes.

00:02:38.355 --> 00:02:42.614 align:middle line:90%


00:02:42.614 --> 00:02:46.280 align:middle line:84%
>> The large giraffe at Dabous
has one particularly striking

00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:48.740 align:middle line:90%
detail--

00:02:48.740 --> 00:02:51.228 align:middle line:84%
it seems to be tethered
by a length of rope

00:02:51.228 --> 00:02:52.145 align:middle line:90%
attached to its snout.

00:02:52.145 --> 00:02:56.840 align:middle line:90%


00:02:56.840 --> 00:02:59.910 align:middle line:84%
The graven line reaches
to the animal's hooves

00:02:59.910 --> 00:03:01.285 align:middle line:90%
and is reminiscent of a lead.

00:03:01.285 --> 00:03:11.110 align:middle line:90%


00:03:11.110 --> 00:03:13.395 align:middle line:84%
The same detail is visible
on the smaller giraffe.

00:03:13.395 --> 00:03:20.170 align:middle line:90%


00:03:20.170 --> 00:03:22.210 align:middle line:84%
If we assume these
lines to represent

00:03:22.210 --> 00:03:24.730 align:middle line:84%
a tether or an
accessory allowing a man

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:27.550 align:middle line:84%
to control the
animal, this implies

00:03:27.550 --> 00:03:32.020 align:middle line:84%
that at one time giraffes
may have been domesticated,

00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:33.290 align:middle line:90%
which seems unlikely.

00:03:33.290 --> 00:03:38.160 align:middle line:90%


00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:43.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Most rock art experts have
a different interpretation.

00:03:43.900 --> 00:03:45.700 align:middle line:90%
The tether is a symbolic one.

00:03:45.700 --> 00:03:50.180 align:middle line:90%


00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:53.660 align:middle line:84%
In this picture, man is linked
to a beast which he admires.

00:03:53.660 --> 00:03:56.540 align:middle line:90%


00:03:56.540 --> 00:04:00.040 align:middle line:84%
It can be a simple
artist's tribute, but also

00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:05.720 align:middle line:84%
a work with magical,
even mystical, qualities.

00:04:05.720 --> 00:04:08.900 align:middle line:84%
The size and detail of the
carvings are in any case

00:04:08.900 --> 00:04:11.750 align:middle line:84%
an appropriate representation
of the importance

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:13.987 align:middle line:90%
of the giraffe in man's psyche.

00:04:13.987 --> 00:04:19.454 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:19.454 --> 00:04:27.406 align:middle line:90%


00:04:27.406 --> 00:04:30.950 align:middle line:84%
>> One has to imagine
how, in the dawn of time,

00:04:30.950 --> 00:04:33.240 align:middle line:84%
man would have felt
before these animals,

00:04:33.240 --> 00:04:35.910 align:middle line:84%
which dwarfed him
in size and power.

00:04:35.910 --> 00:04:39.180 align:middle line:90%


00:04:39.180 --> 00:04:41.340 align:middle line:84%
His initial feeling
was probably that they

00:04:41.340 --> 00:04:42.810 align:middle line:90%
had greater powers than him.

00:04:42.810 --> 00:05:08.160 align:middle line:90%


00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:10.790 align:middle line:84%
Above all, animals
are a mystery to man.

00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:13.940 align:middle line:90%


00:05:13.940 --> 00:05:16.370 align:middle line:84%
All over the world, this
is the principal theme

00:05:16.370 --> 00:05:19.590 align:middle line:84%
in primitive rock art,
the place that animals

00:05:19.590 --> 00:05:21.090 align:middle line:90%
have in the minds of men.

00:05:21.090 --> 00:05:25.330 align:middle line:90%


00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:28.190 align:middle line:84%
The art shows the game
they wish to hunt,

00:05:28.190 --> 00:05:30.280 align:middle line:84%
but also these
mysterious beings they

00:05:30.280 --> 00:05:33.433 align:middle line:84%
would meet in the forests that
made such an impression on.

00:05:33.433 --> 00:05:38.746 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:38.746 --> 00:05:45.991 align:middle line:90%


00:05:45.991 --> 00:05:51.500 align:middle line:84%
>> These are rock carvings left
by Indians on Vancouver Island,

00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:55.370 align:middle line:90%
off Canada's Pacific coast.

00:05:55.370 --> 00:05:58.350 align:middle line:84%
They are several
thousand years old.

00:05:58.350 --> 00:06:02.500 align:middle line:84%
The images of cats,
wolves, birds of prey,

00:06:02.500 --> 00:06:05.210 align:middle line:84%
enhance the attribute or
behavior which most impressed

00:06:05.210 --> 00:06:08.060 align:middle line:90%
men about these beasts--

00:06:08.060 --> 00:06:12.720 align:middle line:84%
the wolf's predatory posture,
the eagle's carnassial beak.

00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:22.182 align:middle line:90%


00:06:22.182 --> 00:06:26.200 align:middle line:84%
>> We see the eagle again here
on these wooden totem poles

00:06:26.200 --> 00:06:29.560 align:middle line:84%
around which the tribes
used to congregate.

00:06:29.560 --> 00:06:32.612 align:middle line:84%
The eyes and the beak
are hugely exaggerated.

00:06:32.612 --> 00:06:42.740 align:middle line:90%


00:06:42.740 --> 00:06:45.360 align:middle line:84%
When a beast was
represented on a totem pole,

00:06:45.360 --> 00:06:47.790 align:middle line:90%
it became sacred to the tribe.

00:06:47.790 --> 00:06:50.280 align:middle line:84%
It was forbidden to kill
it or eat its flesh.

00:06:50.280 --> 00:06:54.080 align:middle line:90%


00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:55.820 align:middle line:84%
The totemized
animal thus becomes

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:58.681 align:middle line:90%
the first sacred animal.

00:06:58.681 --> 00:07:02.577 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:02.577 --> 00:07:07.950 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:07:07.950 --> 00:07:10.630 align:middle line:84%
When a tribe chose
its totem creature,

00:07:10.630 --> 00:07:14.020 align:middle line:84%
it was because it recognized
itself in that creature.

00:07:14.020 --> 00:07:15.760 align:middle line:84%
And the animal became
the incarnation

00:07:15.760 --> 00:07:19.660 align:middle line:90%
of the tribe's characteristics.

00:07:19.660 --> 00:07:21.940 align:middle line:84%
On these totem poles
in Vancouver's Museum

00:07:21.940 --> 00:07:26.590 align:middle line:84%
of Anthropology, it's difficult
to distinguish man from beast.

00:07:26.590 --> 00:07:29.120 align:middle line:84%
It has become hard to tell
who has taken characteristics

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:29.920 align:middle line:90%
from whom.

00:07:29.920 --> 00:07:37.600 align:middle line:90%


00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:40.390 align:middle line:84%
The totem creature becomes
the tribe's forefather,

00:07:40.390 --> 00:07:43.220 align:middle line:90%
its ancestor.

00:07:43.220 --> 00:07:45.710 align:middle line:84%
It is most commonly
a powerful animal

00:07:45.710 --> 00:07:47.450 align:middle line:84%
to which they
associated themselves

00:07:47.450 --> 00:07:50.308 align:middle line:84%
by the wearing of masks
during their ceremonies.

00:07:50.308 --> 00:07:59.092 align:middle line:90%


00:07:59.092 --> 00:08:03.070 align:middle line:84%
>> The representation of animals
as sacred by means of totem

00:08:03.070 --> 00:08:06.070 align:middle line:84%
poles is common to a
great many civilizations.

00:08:06.070 --> 00:08:09.710 align:middle line:90%


00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:13.660 align:middle line:84%
These masks at the Manega
Museum in Burkina Faso

00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:15.910 align:middle line:84%
show us some of the animals
which would have been

00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:17.950 align:middle line:90%
sacred in African societies.

00:08:17.950 --> 00:08:24.440 align:middle line:90%


00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:28.490 align:middle line:84%
The origins of these strong
links between man and beast

00:08:28.490 --> 00:08:30.980 align:middle line:84%
are often linked to the
oral history of a people.

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:41.606 align:middle line:90%


00:08:41.606 --> 00:08:45.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Several dozen crocodiles
live in this pond in Bazoule

00:08:45.490 --> 00:08:46.930 align:middle line:90%
in the heart of Burkina Faso.

00:08:46.930 --> 00:08:54.260 align:middle line:90%


00:08:54.260 --> 00:08:56.270 align:middle line:84%
Despite the presence
of the crocodiles,

00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:59.030 align:middle line:84%
the young men of the village
come here to fish every day.

00:08:59.030 --> 00:09:05.860 align:middle line:90%


00:09:05.860 --> 00:09:07.810 align:middle line:84%
Engrossed in their
work, which involves

00:09:07.810 --> 00:09:10.840 align:middle line:84%
catching the fish in a
hoop, the young fishermen

00:09:10.840 --> 00:09:15.100 align:middle line:84%
pay little attention
to the crocodiles.

00:09:15.100 --> 00:09:17.060 align:middle line:84%
They are just a part
of everyday life.

00:09:17.060 --> 00:09:21.335 align:middle line:90%


00:09:21.335 --> 00:09:24.185 align:middle line:90%
[CROCODILES GROWLING]

00:09:24.185 --> 00:09:27.600 align:middle line:10%
>> Some of these Nile crocodiles
can grow to almost four meters

00:09:27.600 --> 00:09:31.260 align:middle line:10%
long, and can easily carry
off one of the wild beast that

00:09:31.260 --> 00:09:32.880 align:middle line:10%
cross the pond twice a day.

00:09:32.880 --> 00:09:38.930 align:middle line:90%


00:09:38.930 --> 00:09:42.488 align:middle line:84%
Despite the potential danger
to children and livestock,

00:09:42.488 --> 00:09:44.030 align:middle line:84%
no one thinks of
getting rid of them.

00:09:44.030 --> 00:09:48.120 align:middle line:90%


00:09:48.120 --> 00:09:52.434 align:middle line:84%
They have the rather enviable
status of sacred creatures.

00:09:52.434 --> 00:09:55.400 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:55.400 --> 00:09:57.430 align:middle line:84%
All of this is linked
to a story the Mossi

00:09:57.430 --> 00:10:01.788 align:middle line:84%
community has passed down from
one generation to the next.

00:10:01.788 --> 00:10:05.540 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:10:05.540 --> 00:10:08.980 align:middle line:84%
>> The village of Bazoule was
founded several centuries ago

00:10:08.980 --> 00:10:14.311 align:middle line:84%
by a certain Naba Kouba who was
reputedly a fearsome warrior.

00:10:14.311 --> 00:10:16.960 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:10:16.960 --> 00:10:21.370 align:middle line:84%
In the twilight of his life, he
vowed he would be reincarnated.

00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:25.510 align:middle line:84%
And he chose a creature in
which he recognized himself--

00:10:25.510 --> 00:10:30.940 align:middle line:84%
a crocodile, a powerful
and terrifying beast.

00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:33.760 align:middle line:84%
No one knows which
crocodile holds Naba Kouba's

00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:36.670 align:middle line:90%
reincarnated spirit.

00:10:36.670 --> 00:10:39.375 align:middle line:84%
And so all crocodiles
are venerated.

00:10:39.375 --> 00:10:42.105 align:middle line:90%


00:10:42.105 --> 00:10:46.160 align:middle line:84%
>> As is often the case, the
original spiritual tradition

00:10:46.160 --> 00:10:49.760 align:middle line:84%
has grown into a
local superstition.

00:10:49.760 --> 00:10:52.340 align:middle line:84%
In a place where
water is so precious,

00:10:52.340 --> 00:10:55.220 align:middle line:84%
it's believed that
crocodiles must be protected.

00:10:55.220 --> 00:10:59.930 align:middle line:84%
For while they remain, the
pond will never dry up.

00:10:59.930 --> 00:11:02.060 align:middle line:84%
The birth of any
new baby crocodile

00:11:02.060 --> 00:11:04.958 align:middle line:84%
is seen as a sign, a
blessing, a good omen

00:11:04.958 --> 00:11:06.375 align:middle line:84%
for the prosperity
of the village.

00:11:06.375 --> 00:11:09.580 align:middle line:90%


00:11:09.580 --> 00:11:12.550 align:middle line:84%
This man is responsible for
maintaining good relations

00:11:12.550 --> 00:11:15.010 align:middle line:84%
with the sacred crocodiles
by offering them gifts.

00:11:15.010 --> 00:11:32.325 align:middle line:90%


00:11:32.325 --> 00:11:35.380 align:middle line:84%
>> These incredible scenes
are an echo of something that

00:11:35.380 --> 00:11:38.980 align:middle line:84%
happened several
thousand years before.

00:11:38.980 --> 00:11:41.980 align:middle line:10%
In ancient Egypt,
when travelers would

00:11:41.980 --> 00:11:44.590 align:middle line:10%
make a detour via
the city of Shedet,

00:11:44.590 --> 00:11:48.070 align:middle line:10%
also known as Crocodilopolis,
to witness the feeding

00:11:48.070 --> 00:11:49.790 align:middle line:10%
of the sacred crocodile.

00:11:49.790 --> 00:11:56.170 align:middle line:90%


00:11:56.170 --> 00:12:00.190 align:middle line:84%
Only one crocodile was
chosen to be the sacred one.

00:12:00.190 --> 00:12:03.640 align:middle line:90%
But its status was exceptional.

00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:05.810 align:middle line:84%
It was even said to have
worn golden bracelets

00:12:05.810 --> 00:12:06.610 align:middle line:90%
on its forelegs.

00:12:06.610 --> 00:12:15.075 align:middle line:90%


00:12:15.075 --> 00:12:18.620 align:middle line:84%
>> It was an animal which
occupied a very special place

00:12:18.620 --> 00:12:22.490 align:middle line:90%
in Egyptian civilization.

00:12:22.490 --> 00:12:25.100 align:middle line:84%
It is omnipresent throughout
religions and cults

00:12:25.100 --> 00:12:27.560 align:middle line:90%
over 5,000 years.

00:12:27.560 --> 00:12:30.410 align:middle line:84%
But its role within
those religions and cults

00:12:30.410 --> 00:12:33.110 align:middle line:84%
will evolve a great deal
over the changing dynasties.

00:12:33.110 --> 00:12:37.820 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:37.820 --> 00:12:43.580 align:middle line:90%


00:12:43.580 --> 00:12:47.180 align:middle line:84%
>> In primitive times the
Egyptians, like many others,

00:12:47.180 --> 00:12:49.145 align:middle line:84%
worshipped animals
as actual gods.

00:12:49.145 --> 00:12:54.510 align:middle line:90%


00:12:54.510 --> 00:12:57.150 align:middle line:10%
These beliefs were often
specific to provinces,

00:12:57.150 --> 00:13:00.060 align:middle line:10%
or nomes, and the
entire province

00:13:00.060 --> 00:13:02.470 align:middle line:10%
would worship the same animal.

00:13:02.470 --> 00:13:03.720 align:middle line:90%
It was a form of totemism.

00:13:03.720 --> 00:13:08.139 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:08.139 --> 00:13:15.030 align:middle line:90%


00:13:15.030 --> 00:13:17.640 align:middle line:84%
As human society
gradually developed,

00:13:17.640 --> 00:13:21.810 align:middle line:84%
man's dominance over beast
became a reality to all.

00:13:21.810 --> 00:13:28.730 align:middle line:84%
And deities started to take
on human form, while still

00:13:28.730 --> 00:13:31.460 align:middle line:84%
keeping the heads of the
animal gods of previous times.

00:13:31.460 --> 00:13:36.460 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:38.560 align:middle line:84%
Anubis, the god
of the underworld,

00:13:38.560 --> 00:13:41.140 align:middle line:84%
is represented with
the head of a jackal.

00:13:41.140 --> 00:13:46.530 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:13:46.530 --> 00:13:57.310 align:middle line:90%


00:13:57.310 --> 00:14:01.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Most animal species are
represented in Egypt's crowded

00:14:01.040 --> 00:14:04.490 align:middle line:84%
pantheon of gods, with the
notable exception of the horse.

00:14:04.490 --> 00:14:07.280 align:middle line:90%


00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:10.730 align:middle line:84%
If it has pride of place
on this mural at Karnak,

00:14:10.730 --> 00:14:13.670 align:middle line:84%
it is merely as a
literal representation--

00:14:13.670 --> 00:14:16.220 align:middle line:84%
harness to the war
chariot of Ramses II

00:14:16.220 --> 00:14:17.220 align:middle line:90%
at the Battle of Kadesh.

00:14:17.220 --> 00:14:23.920 align:middle line:90%


00:14:23.920 --> 00:14:29.080 align:middle line:84%
However, on the bas relief, one
can see a lion-headed deity.

00:14:29.080 --> 00:14:31.500 align:middle line:84%
This is Sekhmet,
the goddess of war.

00:14:31.500 --> 00:14:46.907 align:middle line:90%


00:14:46.907 --> 00:14:50.610 align:middle line:84%
>> In later times, though gods
became routinely represented

00:14:50.610 --> 00:14:55.760 align:middle line:84%
in human form, animal imagery
did not disappear completely.

00:14:55.760 --> 00:14:58.090 align:middle line:90%
But the role of animals changed.

00:14:58.090 --> 00:15:01.420 align:middle line:84%
They became companions to
the gods, their familiars.

00:15:01.420 --> 00:15:04.460 align:middle line:90%


00:15:04.460 --> 00:15:06.770 align:middle line:90%
They took on a symbolic role.

00:15:06.770 --> 00:15:09.980 align:middle line:84%
Like these baboons at the
foot of the Obelisk at Luxor

00:15:09.980 --> 00:15:12.740 align:middle line:84%
and at the Temple
at Karnak, where

00:15:12.740 --> 00:15:15.110 align:middle line:84%
they are depicted in
a sun-worshiping pose.

00:15:15.110 --> 00:15:27.385 align:middle line:90%


00:15:27.385 --> 00:15:31.340 align:middle line:84%
>> The baboon appears as a
manifestation of the God Thoth,

00:15:31.340 --> 00:15:33.925 align:middle line:90%
god of science and writing.

00:15:33.925 --> 00:15:36.580 align:middle line:84%
But the ape is not
a god in itself--

00:15:36.580 --> 00:15:39.670 align:middle line:84%
merely an image of a
god, a kind of learning

00:15:39.670 --> 00:15:43.010 align:middle line:84%
aid which helped people to
understand the abstract concept

00:15:43.010 --> 00:15:43.810 align:middle line:90%
of divinity.

00:15:43.810 --> 00:15:49.266 align:middle line:90%


00:15:49.266 --> 00:15:52.890 align:middle line:84%
>> In ancient Egypt, there was
a remarkable difference between

00:15:52.890 --> 00:15:55.770 align:middle line:84%
the religious practices of
the pharaoh's court and that

00:15:55.770 --> 00:15:58.620 align:middle line:90%
of the populace.

00:15:58.620 --> 00:16:01.380 align:middle line:84%
Between the complexities of
the pantheon, which the priests

00:16:01.380 --> 00:16:03.090 align:middle line:90%
explained, and peasant beliefs.

00:16:03.090 --> 00:16:13.160 align:middle line:90%


00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:15.530 align:middle line:84%
For instance, the cat
was for a long time

00:16:15.530 --> 00:16:17.150 align:middle line:84%
absent from the
official religion.

00:16:17.150 --> 00:16:30.770 align:middle line:90%


00:16:30.770 --> 00:16:35.380 align:middle line:84%
The peasants referred to cats
as the lions of the poor.

00:16:35.380 --> 00:16:37.690 align:middle line:84%
They were appreciated
as household pets,

00:16:37.690 --> 00:16:39.430 align:middle line:84%
as they got rid of
rats and snakes.

00:16:39.430 --> 00:16:43.220 align:middle line:90%


00:16:43.220 --> 00:16:46.290 align:middle line:84%
The cat eventually became the
subject of a popular cult.

00:16:46.290 --> 00:16:51.735 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:16:51.735 --> 00:16:54.705 align:middle line:90%


00:16:54.705 --> 00:16:59.730 align:middle line:84%
>> It was here at Tell Basta
in the Nile Delta that the cult

00:16:59.730 --> 00:17:04.589 align:middle line:84%
really began 1,000 years before
the birth of Jesus Christ.

00:17:04.589 --> 00:17:09.020 align:middle line:84%
It reached its peak
eight centuries later.

00:17:09.020 --> 00:17:13.520 align:middle line:84%
The town was then
known as Bubastis.

00:17:13.520 --> 00:17:15.710 align:middle line:84%
It was under the patronage
of the Goddess Bastet.

00:17:15.710 --> 00:17:19.819 align:middle line:90%


00:17:19.819 --> 00:17:25.089 align:middle line:84%
Bastet was the goddess
of the sun and fertility.

00:17:25.089 --> 00:17:30.970 align:middle line:84%
She was represented as a
woman with the head of a cat.

00:17:30.970 --> 00:17:34.750 align:middle line:84%
At Bubastis, cats were seen
as the earthly manifestation

00:17:34.750 --> 00:17:37.415 align:middle line:84%
of the goddess, and so
were considered sacred.

00:17:37.415 --> 00:17:44.484 align:middle line:90%


00:17:44.484 --> 00:17:47.035 align:middle line:84%
>> The Temple of Bastet once
stood at the site of these

00:17:47.035 --> 00:17:47.835 align:middle line:90%
ruins.

00:17:47.835 --> 00:17:52.950 align:middle line:90%


00:17:52.950 --> 00:17:55.680 align:middle line:84%
There was also a big
cemetery where cats were

00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:57.390 align:middle line:90%
buried after being mummified.

00:17:57.390 --> 00:18:02.870 align:middle line:90%


00:18:02.870 --> 00:18:04.850 align:middle line:84%
The city was pillaged
and very little

00:18:04.850 --> 00:18:06.581 align:middle line:90%
remains of its treasures.

00:18:06.581 --> 00:18:09.230 align:middle line:90%


00:18:09.230 --> 00:18:12.830 align:middle line:84%
All of the cat mummies
were stolen or destroyed,

00:18:12.830 --> 00:18:15.230 align:middle line:84%
but others have
been found elsewhere

00:18:15.230 --> 00:18:18.784 align:middle line:84%
because cat worship eventually
spread to the whole of Egypt.

00:18:18.784 --> 00:18:24.218 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:24.218 --> 00:18:40.026 align:middle line:90%


00:18:40.026 --> 00:18:43.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Studies of some of these
mummies reveal that some

00:18:43.620 --> 00:18:47.130 align:middle line:84%
of these cats were very young,
which implies that they did not

00:18:47.130 --> 00:18:48.270 align:middle line:90%
die a natural death.

00:18:48.270 --> 00:18:54.510 align:middle line:90%


00:18:54.510 --> 00:18:57.920 align:middle line:90%
X-rays confirm this hypothesis.

00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:01.190 align:middle line:84%
This cat clearly has
fractured vertebrae,

00:19:01.190 --> 00:19:02.510 align:middle line:90%
clearly the cause of death.

00:19:02.510 --> 00:19:11.744 align:middle line:90%


00:19:11.744 --> 00:19:14.880 align:middle line:10%
>> It seems shocking that
cats, which were worshipped,

00:19:14.880 --> 00:19:17.730 align:middle line:10%
were also the
victims of sacrifice.

00:19:17.730 --> 00:19:20.340 align:middle line:10%
There are two theories.

00:19:20.340 --> 00:19:23.100 align:middle line:10%
One is that the cat population
got so out of control

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:25.410 align:middle line:10%
that a form of
euthanasia was performed

00:19:25.410 --> 00:19:26.650 align:middle line:10%
to keep their numbers down.

00:19:26.650 --> 00:19:34.620 align:middle line:90%


00:19:34.620 --> 00:19:38.730 align:middle line:84%
But a more cynical explanation
is that temple officials

00:19:38.730 --> 00:19:42.030 align:middle line:84%
practiced the breeding and
slaughter of cats in order

00:19:42.030 --> 00:19:45.030 align:middle line:84%
to make mummies,
which they then sold

00:19:45.030 --> 00:19:49.140 align:middle line:84%
to pilgrims, who in their
turn used them as offerings

00:19:49.140 --> 00:19:50.100 align:middle line:90%
to the cat goddess.

00:19:50.100 --> 00:19:55.860 align:middle line:90%


00:19:55.860 --> 00:20:00.100 align:middle line:84%
>> All sorts of other
animals were mummified--

00:20:00.100 --> 00:20:05.455 align:middle line:90%
dogs, fish, shrews, gazelles.

00:20:05.455 --> 00:20:11.700 align:middle line:90%


00:20:11.700 --> 00:20:14.880 align:middle line:84%
Hundreds of thousands of
animals in ancient Egypt

00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:18.525 align:middle line:84%
were victims of this tragic
yet prestigious treatment.

00:20:18.525 --> 00:20:21.320 align:middle line:90%


00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:25.440 align:middle line:84%
These baboon corpses are among
the most moving and spectacular

00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:26.240 align:middle line:90%
examples.

00:20:26.240 --> 00:20:30.614 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:20:30.614 --> 00:20:41.792 align:middle line:90%


00:20:41.792 --> 00:20:45.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Some of these apes died of
old age in their master's homes

00:20:45.870 --> 00:20:47.490 align:middle line:90%
or in the temples.

00:20:47.490 --> 00:20:49.340 align:middle line:84%
But the majority
were sacrificed.

00:20:49.340 --> 00:20:55.730 align:middle line:90%


00:20:55.730 --> 00:20:59.430 align:middle line:84%
In Hermopolis in the
underground animal necropolises,

00:20:59.430 --> 00:21:04.900 align:middle line:84%
archaeologists have discovered
thousands of mummified baboons,

00:21:04.900 --> 00:21:07.310 align:middle line:84%
as well as a similar
number of mummified ibises.

00:21:07.310 --> 00:21:12.180 align:middle line:90%


00:21:12.180 --> 00:21:15.360 align:middle line:84%
The baboon and the
Ibis, both creatures

00:21:15.360 --> 00:21:17.550 align:middle line:84%
closely linked to the
God of Hermopolis, Thoth.

00:21:17.550 --> 00:21:22.389 align:middle line:90%


00:21:22.389 --> 00:21:26.350 align:middle line:84%
>> While the Egyptian pantheon
of gods became over millennia

00:21:26.350 --> 00:21:29.890 align:middle line:84%
extremely complex, it was
actually founded on the most

00:21:29.890 --> 00:21:32.208 align:middle line:90%
basic principles of observation.

00:21:32.208 --> 00:21:37.580 align:middle line:90%
[SHEEP BLEATING]

00:21:37.580 --> 00:21:40.250 align:middle line:84%
The ibis was
associated with the god

00:21:40.250 --> 00:21:42.740 align:middle line:84%
of writing because
of the precision

00:21:42.740 --> 00:21:47.510 align:middle line:84%
and finesse of its beak,
reminiscent of the styli used

00:21:47.510 --> 00:21:50.870 align:middle line:84%
to trace hieroglyphics
on parchment.

00:21:50.870 --> 00:21:54.020 align:middle line:84%
And because of the current
shape of this beak resembling

00:21:54.020 --> 00:21:56.780 align:middle line:84%
a crescent moon,
Thoth and the ibis

00:21:56.780 --> 00:21:59.160 align:middle line:84%
are always inextricably
linked to the moon.

00:21:59.160 --> 00:22:03.780 align:middle line:90%


00:22:03.780 --> 00:22:07.550 align:middle line:84%
>> And because it can fly,
the bird can reach the gods up

00:22:07.550 --> 00:22:13.100 align:middle line:84%
above, and so naturally
becomes the messenger.

00:22:13.100 --> 00:22:15.380 align:middle line:84%
In Egypt, the Ibis
would forewarn man

00:22:15.380 --> 00:22:16.620 align:middle line:90%
of the flooding of the Nile.

00:22:16.620 --> 00:22:21.910 align:middle line:90%


00:22:21.910 --> 00:22:24.080 align:middle line:84%
In many ancient
civilizations, birds

00:22:24.080 --> 00:22:25.850 align:middle line:84%
became the emissaries
of the gods.

00:22:25.850 --> 00:22:33.800 align:middle line:90%


00:22:33.800 --> 00:22:35.930 align:middle line:84%
In Rome and ancient
Greece, it was

00:22:35.930 --> 00:22:39.860 align:middle line:84%
believed that animals
had no free will,

00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:41.510 align:middle line:84%
that their every
movement and action

00:22:41.510 --> 00:22:43.240 align:middle line:90%
was guided by a divine hand.

00:22:43.240 --> 00:22:47.360 align:middle line:90%


00:22:47.360 --> 00:22:51.677 align:middle line:84%
Priests would observe
their actions and behavior.

00:22:51.677 --> 00:22:53.510 align:middle line:84%
They were convinced
that they were the gods'

00:22:53.510 --> 00:22:54.980 align:middle line:90%
way of communicating with them.

00:22:54.980 --> 00:23:00.282 align:middle line:90%


00:23:00.282 --> 00:23:03.320 align:middle line:84%
>> They would try to interpret
a bird's flight as readily

00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:04.580 align:middle line:90%
as the movements of a lizard.

00:23:04.580 --> 00:23:07.640 align:middle line:90%


00:23:07.640 --> 00:23:11.140 align:middle line:84%
This Roman copy of a
Greek statue by Praxiteles

00:23:11.140 --> 00:23:14.110 align:middle line:84%
shows Apollo watching
the animal's behavior,

00:23:14.110 --> 00:23:16.180 align:middle line:84%
trying to decipher
the god's message.

00:23:16.180 --> 00:23:21.440 align:middle line:90%


00:23:21.440 --> 00:23:27.400 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:27.400 --> 00:23:29.980 align:middle line:84%
This tradition of
animal divination

00:23:29.980 --> 00:23:34.746 align:middle line:84%
endures to this day in several
places around the world.

00:23:34.746 --> 00:23:39.040 align:middle line:84%
>> It can be seen in Western
Africa in the north of Cameroon

00:23:39.040 --> 00:23:42.640 align:middle line:84%
in the village of Rhumsiki,
where a witch doctor predicts

00:23:42.640 --> 00:23:45.440 align:middle line:84%
the future by interpreting
the language of a crab.

00:23:45.440 --> 00:23:50.300 align:middle line:90%


00:23:50.300 --> 00:23:52.244 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:23:52.244 --> 00:23:54.650 align:middle line:90%
>> The idea is quite simple.

00:23:54.650 --> 00:23:57.800 align:middle line:84%
He places the crab in a jar
containing pieces of wood

00:23:57.800 --> 00:23:59.360 align:middle line:90%
laid out in a specific pattern.

00:23:59.360 --> 00:24:00.620 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:24:00.620 --> 00:24:02.790 align:middle line:84%
>> And he waits for
the crab to move them.

00:24:02.790 --> 00:24:08.574 align:middle line:90%


00:24:08.574 --> 00:24:11.466 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:24:11.466 --> 00:24:16.220 align:middle line:84%
>> These men have a firm belief
that the crab at this point

00:24:16.220 --> 00:24:20.255 align:middle line:84%
in time has no will of its own
but is guided by the spirits.

00:24:20.255 --> 00:24:23.690 align:middle line:90%


00:24:23.690 --> 00:24:25.430 align:middle line:84%
To get into the
right frame of mind

00:24:25.430 --> 00:24:27.380 align:middle line:84%
to interpret the
crabs movements,

00:24:27.380 --> 00:24:29.930 align:middle line:84%
the witch doctor inhaled
some hallucinogenic powder.

00:24:29.930 --> 00:24:39.411 align:middle line:90%


00:24:39.411 --> 00:24:42.220 align:middle line:90%
>> [CHANTING]

00:24:42.220 --> 00:24:46.460 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:24:46.460 --> 00:24:56.230 align:middle line:90%


00:24:56.230 --> 00:25:00.040 align:middle line:84%
>> What the crab does, what
the spirits are saying can

00:25:00.040 --> 00:25:03.470 align:middle line:84%
sometimes, as in this case,
be subject to contradictory

00:25:03.470 --> 00:25:04.270 align:middle line:90%
interpretation.

00:25:04.270 --> 00:25:07.564 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:25:07.564 --> 00:25:11.070 align:middle line:84%
>> This time to eliminate
any possible doubt,

00:25:11.070 --> 00:25:13.990 align:middle line:84%
the witch doctor consults
the crab directly,

00:25:13.990 --> 00:25:17.050 align:middle line:84%
asking it to whisper the message
from the beyond into his ear.

00:25:17.050 --> 00:25:21.020 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:25:21.020 --> 00:25:28.726 align:middle line:90%


00:25:28.726 --> 00:25:31.750 align:middle line:84%
>> If the Rhumsiki villagers
seemed to attach an undue

00:25:31.750 --> 00:25:35.200 align:middle line:84%
importance to a seemingly
insignificant creature,

00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:39.340 align:middle line:84%
it is because of one of its
particular characteristics--

00:25:39.340 --> 00:25:40.210 align:middle line:90%
it buries itself.

00:25:40.210 --> 00:25:45.780 align:middle line:90%


00:25:45.780 --> 00:25:48.750 align:middle line:84%
When they see it sink
beneath the earth,

00:25:48.750 --> 00:25:51.150 align:middle line:84%
they imagine it is
consorting with the gods

00:25:51.150 --> 00:25:53.068 align:middle line:90%
of the underworld.

00:25:53.068 --> 00:25:57.514 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:25:57.514 --> 00:26:08.382 align:middle line:90%


00:26:08.382 --> 00:26:11.355 align:middle line:84%
>> Here is another creature
linked forever to subterranean

00:26:11.355 --> 00:26:12.155 align:middle line:90%
powers.

00:26:12.155 --> 00:26:18.260 align:middle line:90%


00:26:18.260 --> 00:26:22.590 align:middle line:84%
The snake is an
animal like no other,

00:26:22.590 --> 00:26:25.590 align:middle line:84%
with a shape reduced
to its most basic form,

00:26:25.590 --> 00:26:30.450 align:middle line:84%
but able to crawl, climb, or
swim, at home in any situation.

00:26:30.450 --> 00:26:35.020 align:middle line:90%


00:26:35.020 --> 00:26:38.630 align:middle line:84%
>> An ambiguous creature which
one never seems to get to grips

00:26:38.630 --> 00:26:40.070 align:middle line:90%
with or get to know.

00:26:40.070 --> 00:26:44.022 align:middle line:90%


00:26:44.022 --> 00:26:47.974 align:middle line:84%
Snakes have always
fascinated man.

00:26:47.974 --> 00:26:50.301 align:middle line:84%
In all the world's
mythologies taken as a whole,

00:26:50.301 --> 00:26:51.926 align:middle line:84%
it is always certainly
the world's most

00:26:51.926 --> 00:26:52.914 align:middle line:90%
venerated creature.

00:26:52.914 --> 00:27:04.280 align:middle line:90%


00:27:04.280 --> 00:27:06.630 align:middle line:84%
In many civilizations,
the snake was

00:27:06.630 --> 00:27:11.260 align:middle line:84%
worshipped as a creating
deity, a great god

00:27:11.260 --> 00:27:15.040 align:middle line:84%
of darkness linked to the chaos
of the origins of existence.

00:27:15.040 --> 00:27:25.578 align:middle line:90%


00:27:25.578 --> 00:27:28.800 align:middle line:10%
>> Many snake deities will
come to take the place of these

00:27:28.800 --> 00:27:31.740 align:middle line:10%
primitive gods.

00:27:31.740 --> 00:27:35.180 align:middle line:84%
They could be good or
evil, capable of the best

00:27:35.180 --> 00:27:35.980 align:middle line:90%
and the worst.

00:27:35.980 --> 00:27:40.150 align:middle line:90%


00:27:40.150 --> 00:27:45.810 align:middle line:84%
In pre-Colombian societies,
the good side was prevalent.

00:27:45.810 --> 00:27:49.100 align:middle line:84%
>> The snake is frequently
represented on Aztec or Mayan

00:27:49.100 --> 00:27:49.900 align:middle line:90%
monuments.

00:27:49.900 --> 00:27:52.970 align:middle line:90%


00:27:52.970 --> 00:27:55.870 align:middle line:10%
It becomes the incarnation
of the civilizing god,

00:27:55.870 --> 00:27:57.730 align:middle line:10%
linked to crops and fertility.

00:27:57.730 --> 00:28:05.720 align:middle line:90%


00:28:05.720 --> 00:28:11.760 align:middle line:84%
It often takes the form
of a winged serpent,

00:28:11.760 --> 00:28:17.900 align:middle line:84%
known by the Aztecs as
Quetzalcoatl and by the Mayans

00:28:17.900 --> 00:28:22.190 align:middle line:84%
as Kukulkan, represented here
holding a head in its jaws.

00:28:22.190 --> 00:28:33.944 align:middle line:90%


00:28:33.944 --> 00:28:37.540 align:middle line:10%
>> Snakes are still worshipped
nowadays in Western Africa.

00:28:37.540 --> 00:28:40.210 align:middle line:90%


00:28:40.210 --> 00:28:42.310 align:middle line:84%
They are the object
of a genuine cult

00:28:42.310 --> 00:28:45.040 align:middle line:84%
in Ouidah, in Southern
Benin's Lake region.

00:28:45.040 --> 00:28:49.140 align:middle line:90%


00:28:49.140 --> 00:28:52.395 align:middle line:84%
Not just any snake, more
specifically-- pythons.

00:28:52.395 --> 00:28:54.900 align:middle line:90%


00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:57.480 align:middle line:84%
There is a temple dedicated
to them behind these walls.

00:28:57.480 --> 00:29:04.845 align:middle line:90%


00:29:04.845 --> 00:29:07.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Within the temple's
inner sanctum,

00:29:07.270 --> 00:29:10.270 align:middle line:84%
the village's wise men come
to pay tribute and respect

00:29:10.270 --> 00:29:13.435 align:middle line:84%
to these sacred pythons,
which they call dangbes.

00:29:13.435 --> 00:29:18.190 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:29:18.190 --> 00:29:21.340 align:middle line:84%
>> This snake worship is
relatively recent here,

00:29:21.340 --> 00:29:22.765 align:middle line:90%
dating back to the 18th century.

00:29:22.765 --> 00:29:26.740 align:middle line:90%


00:29:26.740 --> 00:29:31.360 align:middle line:84%
Two kingdoms were then at war,
the Danxome and the Ouidahs.

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:34.030 align:middle line:90%


00:29:34.030 --> 00:29:36.460 align:middle line:84%
As the Ouidahs were
about to admit defeat,

00:29:36.460 --> 00:29:39.490 align:middle line:84%
thousands of pythons are said
to have come out of the forest

00:29:39.490 --> 00:29:43.250 align:middle line:90%
and put the Danxome to flight.

00:29:43.250 --> 00:29:45.780 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL SINGING]

00:29:45.780 --> 00:29:49.200 align:middle line:84%
>> The king of the Ouidahs
wanted to thank the pythons

00:29:49.200 --> 00:29:51.290 align:middle line:84%
and build a temple
dedicated to them.

00:29:51.290 --> 00:29:55.682 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL SINGING]

00:29:55.682 --> 00:30:03.650 align:middle line:90%


00:30:03.650 --> 00:30:07.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Ever since, this small
circular building has housed

00:30:07.710 --> 00:30:10.070 align:middle line:90%
a few sacred specimens.

00:30:10.070 --> 00:30:13.580 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL SINGING]

00:30:13.580 --> 00:30:25.990 align:middle line:90%


00:30:25.990 --> 00:30:28.870 align:middle line:84%
The python's temple
is directly opposite

00:30:28.870 --> 00:30:31.090 align:middle line:90%
the Christian cathedral.

00:30:31.090 --> 00:30:35.200 align:middle line:84%
Over the road, the snake is not
accorded the same privileges

00:30:35.200 --> 00:30:38.336 align:middle line:84%
nor is it seen in such
a benevolent light.

00:30:38.336 --> 00:30:42.240 align:middle line:90%
[RELIGIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:30:42.240 --> 00:30:46.632 align:middle line:90%


00:30:46.632 --> 00:30:50.840 align:middle line:84%
>> In the Bible, the
snake represents evil.

00:30:50.840 --> 00:30:52.480 align:middle line:84%
The snake tempted
the first woman

00:30:52.480 --> 00:30:54.310 align:middle line:84%
into tasting the
forbidden fruit,

00:30:54.310 --> 00:30:57.620 align:middle line:84%
so depriving man of
paradise on Earth.

00:30:57.620 --> 00:30:59.960 align:middle line:84%
Paradoxically, the snake
is the only creature

00:30:59.960 --> 00:31:03.664 align:middle line:84%
to play an active role
in the scriptures.

00:31:03.664 --> 00:31:07.236 align:middle line:84%
All the other creatures appear
in merely symbolic roles.

00:31:07.236 --> 00:31:11.204 align:middle line:90%
[RELIGIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:11.204 --> 00:31:17.170 align:middle line:90%


00:31:17.170 --> 00:31:19.660 align:middle line:84%
The animals which appear
the most in the Bible

00:31:19.660 --> 00:31:21.580 align:middle line:84%
are the ones that men
most often encountered

00:31:21.580 --> 00:31:22.810 align:middle line:90%
in their daily lives.

00:31:22.810 --> 00:31:26.040 align:middle line:90%
[BELL RINGING]

00:31:26.040 --> 00:31:28.970 align:middle line:84%
They are remembered for
the image they convey.

00:31:28.970 --> 00:31:31.736 align:middle line:90%
They have a symbolic value.

00:31:31.736 --> 00:31:35.260 align:middle line:84%
>> The bee is identified
with hard work,

00:31:35.260 --> 00:31:38.680 align:middle line:84%
the dove with innocence,
and the ewe with gentleness.

00:31:38.680 --> 00:31:44.350 align:middle line:90%
[SHEEP BLEATING]

00:31:44.350 --> 00:31:47.650 align:middle line:84%
And so to help to
convey the message,

00:31:47.650 --> 00:31:51.490 align:middle line:84%
the Holy Spirit is shown as a
dove, and the children of God

00:31:51.490 --> 00:31:54.040 align:middle line:84%
are represented as
sheep led by a shepherd.

00:31:54.040 --> 00:32:00.090 align:middle line:90%
[RELIGIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:32:00.090 --> 00:32:15.385 align:middle line:90%


00:32:15.385 --> 00:32:19.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Other creatures, however, are
used to convey negative images,

00:32:19.680 --> 00:32:22.530 align:middle line:90%
such as sin, temptation.

00:32:22.530 --> 00:32:27.110 align:middle line:84%
They become the
incarnation of evil,

00:32:27.110 --> 00:32:29.980 align:middle line:84%
like these rats depicted
devouring the world

00:32:29.980 --> 00:32:32.110 align:middle line:84%
on the Church of
Saint-Germain-l'Auxerrois in

00:32:32.110 --> 00:32:32.910 align:middle line:90%
Paris.

00:32:32.910 --> 00:32:42.390 align:middle line:90%


00:32:42.390 --> 00:32:45.000 align:middle line:84%
Because the wolf eats
sheep, it automatically

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:48.380 align:middle line:84%
becomes the devil himself,
attacking the Lord's flock.

00:32:48.380 --> 00:32:53.180 align:middle line:90%


00:32:53.180 --> 00:32:57.620 align:middle line:84%
>> In the 13th century in
the Gubbio region of Italy,

00:32:57.620 --> 00:33:00.687 align:middle line:84%
the devil incarnate was a
huge wolf spreading terror

00:33:00.687 --> 00:33:01.520 align:middle line:90%
throughout the land.

00:33:01.520 --> 00:33:04.230 align:middle line:90%


00:33:04.230 --> 00:33:07.080 align:middle line:10%
The story goes that
Saint Francis of Assisi

00:33:07.080 --> 00:33:09.940 align:middle line:10%
convinced the wolf
to stop doing wrong

00:33:09.940 --> 00:33:13.756 align:middle line:10%
and that the repentant wolf
became as meek as a lamb.

00:33:13.756 --> 00:33:18.948 align:middle line:90%


00:33:18.948 --> 00:33:23.050 align:middle line:10%
>> Usually, people kept away
from supposedly evil animals

00:33:23.050 --> 00:33:26.480 align:middle line:10%
for fear of being
accused of witchcraft.

00:33:26.480 --> 00:33:30.070 align:middle line:84%
It was best to stay away
from rams or black cats.

00:33:30.070 --> 00:33:32.360 align:middle line:84%
However, the cat was
venerated in the town of Ypres

00:33:32.360 --> 00:33:33.160 align:middle line:90%
in Belgium.

00:33:33.160 --> 00:33:38.790 align:middle line:90%


00:33:38.790 --> 00:33:41.580 align:middle line:84%
When this region
converted to Christianity,

00:33:41.580 --> 00:33:43.320 align:middle line:84%
the religious
authorities demanded

00:33:43.320 --> 00:33:45.060 align:middle line:84%
that the town proved
it had renounced

00:33:45.060 --> 00:33:51.570 align:middle line:84%
the cult of cat worship,
which it had celebrated

00:33:51.570 --> 00:33:54.120 align:middle line:84%
at great festivals where
live cats were thrown

00:33:54.120 --> 00:33:55.500 align:middle line:90%
from the top of this tower.

00:33:55.500 --> 00:33:58.422 align:middle line:90%


00:33:58.422 --> 00:34:02.000 align:middle line:84%
>> A practice which lasted
until the 19th century.

00:34:02.000 --> 00:34:05.400 align:middle line:84%
Nowadays, the tradition
is held by this jester,

00:34:05.400 --> 00:34:07.500 align:middle line:84%
throwing soft toy
cats from the tower.

00:34:07.500 --> 00:34:15.542 align:middle line:90%


00:34:15.542 --> 00:34:19.518 align:middle line:90%
[CROWDS CHEERING]

00:34:19.518 --> 00:34:35.440 align:middle line:90%


00:34:35.440 --> 00:34:38.570 align:middle line:84%
Every three years, Ypres
celebrates its cat festival.

00:34:38.570 --> 00:34:41.199 align:middle line:90%


00:34:41.199 --> 00:34:44.120 align:middle line:84%
It no longer has anything
to do with the sacred.

00:34:44.120 --> 00:34:46.489 align:middle line:84%
It has become a purely
pagan and festive occasion.

00:34:46.489 --> 00:34:57.330 align:middle line:90%


00:34:57.330 --> 00:34:59.640 align:middle line:10%
Throughout the
Christian West, the link

00:34:59.640 --> 00:35:01.920 align:middle line:10%
between animals and
religion has faded

00:35:01.920 --> 00:35:04.020 align:middle line:10%
to the point where
it only exists

00:35:04.020 --> 00:35:06.706 align:middle line:10%
as the echo of a distant memory.

00:35:06.706 --> 00:35:10.087 align:middle line:90%
[DRUMS BEATING]

00:35:10.087 --> 00:35:17.815 align:middle line:90%


00:35:17.815 --> 00:35:21.290 align:middle line:10%
>> In India, however, this
powerful and intimate link

00:35:21.290 --> 00:35:24.050 align:middle line:10%
between animals and religious
belief and practice is

00:35:24.050 --> 00:35:25.220 align:middle line:10%
as widespread as ever.

00:35:25.220 --> 00:35:33.670 align:middle line:90%


00:35:33.670 --> 00:35:38.000 align:middle line:84%
The most famous example
being the sacred cow.

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:41.480 align:middle line:90%
[INDIAN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:35:41.480 --> 00:35:44.720 align:middle line:90%


00:35:44.720 --> 00:35:48.090 align:middle line:84%
To understand why this creature
has such an exalted status,

00:35:48.090 --> 00:35:51.545 align:middle line:84%
one must refer back to ancient
Sanskrit texts, the "Vedas."

00:35:51.545 --> 00:35:57.960 align:middle line:90%


00:35:57.960 --> 00:36:00.290 align:middle line:84%
The "Vedas" teach that the
being who gives us milk

00:36:00.290 --> 00:36:01.090 align:middle line:90%
is our mother.

00:36:01.090 --> 00:36:03.660 align:middle line:90%


00:36:03.660 --> 00:36:06.840 align:middle line:84%
Since humans drink
cow's milk, Vedic wisdom

00:36:06.840 --> 00:36:10.138 align:middle line:84%
tells us that the cow must
be accepted, respected,

00:36:10.138 --> 00:36:11.430 align:middle line:90%
and treated as a mother figure.

00:36:11.430 --> 00:36:27.831 align:middle line:90%


00:36:27.831 --> 00:36:31.330 align:middle line:84%
>> The cow, actually
a water Buffalo,

00:36:31.330 --> 00:36:34.480 align:middle line:84%
has been considered sacred in
India since the 5th century BC.

00:36:34.480 --> 00:36:38.200 align:middle line:90%


00:36:38.200 --> 00:36:41.230 align:middle line:84%
Quite recently,
Mahatma Gandhi said,

00:36:41.230 --> 00:36:43.390 align:middle line:84%
any man who does
not believe the cow

00:36:43.390 --> 00:36:47.560 align:middle line:84%
is sacred is not a true
Hindu, because the cow is

00:36:47.560 --> 00:36:50.410 align:middle line:90%
the embodiment of divine order.

00:36:50.410 --> 00:36:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And so cows live a peaceful
and fearless existence

00:36:53.230 --> 00:36:57.340 align:middle line:84%
among India's population, who
may drink or otherwise use

00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:58.680 align:middle line:90%
their milk.

00:36:58.680 --> 00:37:01.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Even their droppings are
seen in a positive light.

00:37:01.500 --> 00:37:06.600 align:middle line:90%


00:37:06.600 --> 00:37:10.060 align:middle line:84%
Cow pats are collected for
heating fuel or building mud

00:37:10.060 --> 00:37:12.338 align:middle line:90%
walls.

00:37:12.338 --> 00:37:16.676 align:middle line:10%
[CAR HORN HONKING]

00:37:16.676 --> 00:37:22.950 align:middle line:90%


00:37:22.950 --> 00:37:26.190 align:middle line:84%
There are nearly 200
million cattle in India,

00:37:26.190 --> 00:37:31.860 align:middle line:84%
approximately 15% of the
world's bovine population.

00:37:31.860 --> 00:37:34.740 align:middle line:84%
As the killing of a cow
is seen in Hindu society

00:37:34.740 --> 00:37:37.650 align:middle line:84%
as a serious offense,
only a few thousand

00:37:37.650 --> 00:37:39.090 align:middle line:90%
end up on the butcher's table.

00:37:39.090 --> 00:37:42.700 align:middle line:90%


00:37:42.700 --> 00:37:45.670 align:middle line:84%
The animals benefit directly
from man's interpretation

00:37:45.670 --> 00:37:46.630 align:middle line:90%
of the sacred texts.

00:37:46.630 --> 00:37:53.568 align:middle line:90%


00:37:53.568 --> 00:37:57.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Here in India, some
religions go even further

00:37:57.820 --> 00:38:00.580 align:middle line:90%
in their respect for animals.

00:38:00.580 --> 00:38:02.755 align:middle line:84%
This woman is a follower
of the Jain religion.

00:38:02.755 --> 00:38:05.990 align:middle line:90%


00:38:05.990 --> 00:38:11.000 align:middle line:84%
There are about five
million Jains in India.

00:38:11.000 --> 00:38:12.455 align:middle line:90%
The religion predates Hinduism.

00:38:12.455 --> 00:38:15.710 align:middle line:90%


00:38:15.710 --> 00:38:19.430 align:middle line:84%
It is a religion based on
non-violence and absolute

00:38:19.430 --> 00:38:23.450 align:middle line:90%
respect for all forms of life.

00:38:23.450 --> 00:38:27.610 align:middle line:10%
>> Unlike Hinduism, Jainism
has no external deity.

00:38:27.610 --> 00:38:31.700 align:middle line:90%


00:38:31.700 --> 00:38:35.840 align:middle line:84%
Jains believe that god is
within every living being,

00:38:35.840 --> 00:38:37.860 align:middle line:84%
and so every life
form is sacred.

00:38:37.860 --> 00:38:46.520 align:middle line:90%


00:38:46.520 --> 00:38:50.000 align:middle line:10%
This nun who officiates in this
temple must wear a mask over

00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:53.085 align:middle line:10%
her face so that she cannot
swallow even the smallest

00:38:53.085 --> 00:38:53.885 align:middle line:10%
insect.

00:38:53.885 --> 00:39:00.510 align:middle line:90%


00:39:00.510 --> 00:39:03.030 align:middle line:84%
Any creature needs merely
the slightest connection

00:39:03.030 --> 00:39:05.460 align:middle line:84%
to a god to be treated
with the greatest

00:39:05.460 --> 00:39:07.488 align:middle line:90%
respect and protection.

00:39:07.488 --> 00:39:13.572 align:middle line:90%


00:39:13.572 --> 00:39:17.400 align:middle line:84%
>> This is particularly true of
these macaque monkeys who have

00:39:17.400 --> 00:39:20.700 align:middle line:84%
a free run of Indian towns
because they are linked

00:39:20.700 --> 00:39:24.580 align:middle line:84%
to Hanuman, the Monkey God,
an important figure in Hindu

00:39:24.580 --> 00:39:25.380 align:middle line:90%
mythology.

00:39:25.380 --> 00:39:33.220 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:33.220 --> 00:39:36.950 align:middle line:10%
In Varanasi, the monkeys have
overrun the Temple of Durga

00:39:36.950 --> 00:39:39.980 align:middle line:10%
to such an extent that it has
become known as the Monkey

00:39:39.980 --> 00:39:43.370 align:middle line:10%
Temple, even though the
Goddess Durga is usually

00:39:43.370 --> 00:39:44.350 align:middle line:10%
linked to the tiger.

00:39:44.350 --> 00:39:50.668 align:middle line:90%


00:39:50.668 --> 00:39:54.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Here, the sanctification
of animals never seems to make

00:39:54.530 --> 00:39:57.780 align:middle line:90%
sense to the non-believer.

00:39:57.780 --> 00:40:00.690 align:middle line:84%
In a country where hygiene
problems are legion,

00:40:00.690 --> 00:40:03.450 align:middle line:84%
there are even places where
rats are considered sacred.

00:40:03.450 --> 00:40:08.785 align:middle line:90%
[INDIAN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:40:08.785 --> 00:40:17.530 align:middle line:90%


00:40:17.530 --> 00:40:19.930 align:middle line:84%
In Deshnok in
Northern Rajasthan,

00:40:19.930 --> 00:40:23.990 align:middle line:84%
this temple houses thousands
of rats, fed and protected

00:40:23.990 --> 00:40:24.790 align:middle line:90%
by their devotees.

00:40:24.790 --> 00:40:28.162 align:middle line:90%


00:40:28.162 --> 00:40:35.617 align:middle line:90%
[BELL RINGS]

00:40:35.617 --> 00:40:39.370 align:middle line:84%
>> The reason for their status
has its roots in an ancient

00:40:39.370 --> 00:40:41.180 align:middle line:90%
folk tale.

00:40:41.180 --> 00:40:44.290 align:middle line:84%
A great many years ago,
a yellow fever epidemic

00:40:44.290 --> 00:40:47.210 align:middle line:90%
killed all the town's children.

00:40:47.210 --> 00:40:49.760 align:middle line:84%
Their desperate parents
pleaded with a local miracle

00:40:49.760 --> 00:40:54.710 align:middle line:84%
worker whose name was Karni Mata
to do something-- and she did.

00:40:54.710 --> 00:40:57.785 align:middle line:84%
She reincarnated all of
the children as rats.

00:40:57.785 --> 00:41:03.605 align:middle line:90%
[INDIAN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:41:03.605 --> 00:41:12.335 align:middle line:90%


00:41:12.335 --> 00:41:15.840 align:middle line:84%
>> In the local dialect,
the same word, Kabba,

00:41:15.840 --> 00:41:18.060 align:middle line:84%
is used for both
children and rats.

00:41:18.060 --> 00:41:28.190 align:middle line:90%


00:41:28.190 --> 00:41:31.800 align:middle line:84%
Because the rats are seen
as the town's own children,

00:41:31.800 --> 00:41:34.400 align:middle line:84%
everybody takes care
of and feeds the rats.

00:41:34.400 --> 00:41:39.320 align:middle line:90%
[INDIAN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:41:39.320 --> 00:41:48.200 align:middle line:90%


00:41:48.200 --> 00:41:50.120 align:middle line:84%
The priests keep a
close eye on the rats

00:41:50.120 --> 00:41:52.094 align:middle line:90%
and look after their well-being.

00:41:52.094 --> 00:41:59.690 align:middle line:90%


00:41:59.690 --> 00:42:02.150 align:middle line:84%
The inner sanctum of the
temple is home to a true

00:42:02.150 --> 00:42:09.600 align:middle line:84%
cult. The faithful worship
both Karni Mata as a goddess

00:42:09.600 --> 00:42:12.652 align:middle line:84%
and the rats who harbor the
souls of their children.

00:42:12.652 --> 00:42:17.572 align:middle line:90%
[INDIAN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:42:17.572 --> 00:42:27.904 align:middle line:90%


00:42:27.904 --> 00:42:30.920 align:middle line:84%
>> On the doors of
this temple at Deshnok,

00:42:30.920 --> 00:42:34.040 align:middle line:84%
the rat is represented alongside
another important mythological

00:42:34.040 --> 00:42:38.720 align:middle line:84%
figure, half man,
half elephant, Ganesh,

00:42:38.720 --> 00:42:41.300 align:middle line:84%
one of the most popular deities
in this part of the world.

00:42:41.300 --> 00:42:45.750 align:middle line:90%


00:42:45.750 --> 00:42:49.630 align:middle line:84%
Ganesh and the rat are
inextricably linked.

00:42:49.630 --> 00:42:52.050 align:middle line:84%
And more often than not are
represented side by side.

00:42:52.050 --> 00:42:55.582 align:middle line:90%


00:42:55.582 --> 00:43:00.650 align:middle line:10%
>> This bizarre holy union has
its origin in mythology where

00:43:00.650 --> 00:43:03.200 align:middle line:10%
the elephant-headed
man, against all logic,

00:43:03.200 --> 00:43:04.940 align:middle line:10%
rides upon the back of the rat.

00:43:04.940 --> 00:43:11.140 align:middle line:90%


00:43:11.140 --> 00:43:13.690 align:middle line:90%
Ganesh is everywhere.

00:43:13.690 --> 00:43:15.440 align:middle line:90%
On walls, near houses.

00:43:15.440 --> 00:43:18.080 align:middle line:90%


00:43:18.080 --> 00:43:20.150 align:middle line:84%
Great temples are
dedicated to him,

00:43:20.150 --> 00:43:21.300 align:middle line:90%
such as this one in Jaipur.

00:43:21.300 --> 00:43:26.400 align:middle line:90%
[BELLS RINGING]

00:43:26.400 --> 00:43:29.340 align:middle line:84%
This temple is so popular
because people consult Ganesh

00:43:29.340 --> 00:43:31.800 align:middle line:90%
about all sorts of things.

00:43:31.800 --> 00:43:33.900 align:middle line:84%
He is the god of
knowledge, but also

00:43:33.900 --> 00:43:39.008 align:middle line:84%
responsible for one's fortunes
in love, exams, or business.

00:43:39.008 --> 00:43:42.291 align:middle line:90%
[BELLS RINGING]

00:43:42.291 --> 00:43:43.229 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:43:43.229 --> 00:43:47.430 align:middle line:84%
>> To gain Ganesh's favor,
the faithful bring gifts,

00:43:47.430 --> 00:43:50.240 align:middle line:84%
which the temple officials
symbolically offer to the god.

00:43:50.240 --> 00:43:53.012 align:middle line:90%


00:43:53.012 --> 00:43:56.570 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:43:56.570 --> 00:44:07.010 align:middle line:90%


00:44:07.010 --> 00:44:10.960 align:middle line:84%
Ganesh is the object of quite a
remarkable level of veneration.

00:44:10.960 --> 00:44:13.050 align:middle line:84%
He's very close to
people's hearts,

00:44:13.050 --> 00:44:15.520 align:middle line:84%
a sort of multi-purpose
god, asked

00:44:15.520 --> 00:44:17.425 align:middle line:84%
to solve all manner
of everyday problems.

00:44:17.425 --> 00:44:20.428 align:middle line:90%


00:44:20.428 --> 00:44:23.860 align:middle line:90%
>> The symbolism is quite clear.

00:44:23.860 --> 00:44:25.740 align:middle line:84%
The animal half of
this hybrid deity

00:44:25.740 --> 00:44:28.470 align:middle line:84%
represents the
elephant's power to move

00:44:28.470 --> 00:44:29.490 align:middle line:90%
the heaviest of burdens.

00:44:29.490 --> 00:44:41.650 align:middle line:90%


00:44:41.650 --> 00:44:44.320 align:middle line:84%
With its size,
strength, and power,

00:44:44.320 --> 00:44:46.450 align:middle line:84%
the elephant could not
fail to make an impression

00:44:46.450 --> 00:44:48.880 align:middle line:84%
on men who were seeking
ways to interpret

00:44:48.880 --> 00:44:50.110 align:middle line:90%
their sacred universe.

00:44:50.110 --> 00:44:53.970 align:middle line:90%


00:44:53.970 --> 00:44:55.560 align:middle line:84%
On top of its
physical attributes,

00:44:55.560 --> 00:44:57.330 align:middle line:84%
the elephant is
considered to benefit

00:44:57.330 --> 00:45:00.330 align:middle line:84%
from innate wisdom, which is
seen as the greatest virtue.

00:45:00.330 --> 00:45:04.234 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:45:04.234 --> 00:45:08.626 align:middle line:90%


00:45:08.626 --> 00:45:13.090 align:middle line:84%
>> In 13th century Thailand,
in the Sukhothai area,

00:45:13.090 --> 00:45:17.890 align:middle line:84%
the king had a Buddhist temple
built, known as Wat Chang Lom,

00:45:17.890 --> 00:45:21.210 align:middle line:84%
which means temple
surrounded by elephants.

00:45:21.210 --> 00:45:26.330 align:middle line:90%


00:45:26.330 --> 00:45:28.670 align:middle line:84%
The base of the
stupa is decorated

00:45:28.670 --> 00:45:33.350 align:middle line:84%
with 36 elephant images, a
demonstration of the reverence

00:45:33.350 --> 00:45:35.150 align:middle line:84%
that Buddhism has
for the elephant.

00:45:35.150 --> 00:45:39.623 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:45:39.623 --> 00:45:52.048 align:middle line:90%


00:45:52.048 --> 00:45:54.960 align:middle line:84%
>> The elephant has played
an important part in the life

00:45:54.960 --> 00:45:57.640 align:middle line:84%
story of Buddha himself,
right from his birth.

00:45:57.640 --> 00:46:03.100 align:middle line:90%


00:46:03.100 --> 00:46:08.710 align:middle line:84%
Buddha is said to have been
born from immaculate conception.

00:46:08.710 --> 00:46:10.810 align:middle line:10%
His mother is supposed
to have been impregnated

00:46:10.810 --> 00:46:12.520 align:middle line:10%
by a white elephant in a dream.

00:46:12.520 --> 00:46:18.900 align:middle line:90%


00:46:18.900 --> 00:46:21.690 align:middle line:84%
The elephant also plays a
part in two other episodes

00:46:21.690 --> 00:46:22.560 align:middle line:90%
of Buddha's life.

00:46:22.560 --> 00:46:25.890 align:middle line:90%


00:46:25.890 --> 00:46:27.870 align:middle line:84%
One is represented
life size here.

00:46:27.870 --> 00:46:33.760 align:middle line:90%


00:46:33.760 --> 00:46:36.910 align:middle line:84%
This statue tells the tale of
how the elephant and the monkey

00:46:36.910 --> 00:46:39.940 align:middle line:84%
tended to Buddha as he
ended one of his long fasts.

00:46:39.940 --> 00:46:50.620 align:middle line:90%


00:46:50.620 --> 00:46:55.750 align:middle line:84%
The monkey is
offering him honey,

00:46:55.750 --> 00:46:58.690 align:middle line:84%
and the elephant is bringing
him water in a bamboo stem.

00:46:58.690 --> 00:47:01.784 align:middle line:90%


00:47:01.784 --> 00:47:05.170 align:middle line:84%
>> The elephant will always
remain linked to Buddha,

00:47:05.170 --> 00:47:06.350 align:middle line:90%
even after his death.

00:47:06.350 --> 00:47:09.090 align:middle line:90%


00:47:09.090 --> 00:47:13.320 align:middle line:84%
Every year at the end of July,
the town of Kandy in Sri Lanka

00:47:13.320 --> 00:47:15.230 align:middle line:90%
is taken over by elephants.

00:47:15.230 --> 00:47:19.490 align:middle line:90%


00:47:19.490 --> 00:47:22.670 align:middle line:84%
They come from the neighboring
villages with their masters

00:47:22.670 --> 00:47:24.920 align:middle line:90%
to take part in Esala Perehera.

00:47:24.920 --> 00:47:28.880 align:middle line:90%


00:47:28.880 --> 00:47:31.280 align:middle line:84%
It's an important
religious festival

00:47:31.280 --> 00:47:34.310 align:middle line:84%
which has been celebrated
for nearly 2,000 years

00:47:34.310 --> 00:47:35.960 align:middle line:90%
and honors the memory of Buddha.

00:47:35.960 --> 00:47:42.070 align:middle line:90%


00:47:42.070 --> 00:47:45.450 align:middle line:84%
>> When Buddha died
in the 6th century BC,

00:47:45.450 --> 00:47:46.455 align:middle line:90%
his body was cremated.

00:47:46.455 --> 00:47:50.660 align:middle line:90%


00:47:50.660 --> 00:47:53.500 align:middle line:84%
A princess is said to have
retrieved one of his teeth

00:47:53.500 --> 00:47:57.320 align:middle line:84%
from the funeral pyre,
hidden it in her hair,

00:47:57.320 --> 00:47:58.910 align:middle line:90%
and taken it back to Sri Lanka.

00:47:58.910 --> 00:48:01.610 align:middle line:90%


00:48:01.610 --> 00:48:04.730 align:middle line:10%
This dental relic has kept
it within the temple known

00:48:04.730 --> 00:48:10.250 align:middle line:10%
as Dalada Maligawa, literally
the temple of the tooth.

00:48:10.250 --> 00:48:14.170 align:middle line:10%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:48:14.170 --> 00:48:21.520 align:middle line:90%


00:48:21.520 --> 00:48:24.430 align:middle line:84%
Since the 18th century,
the precious molar

00:48:24.430 --> 00:48:26.410 align:middle line:84%
is paraded on the
back of an elephant

00:48:26.410 --> 00:48:28.830 align:middle line:84%
during the huge
Perehera celebrations.

00:48:28.830 --> 00:48:35.620 align:middle line:90%


00:48:35.620 --> 00:48:40.470 align:middle line:90%
[BELLS RINGING]

00:48:40.470 --> 00:48:43.070 align:middle line:84%
>> On the evening
of the big day,

00:48:43.070 --> 00:48:45.680 align:middle line:84%
the elephants congregate
on the esplanade in front

00:48:45.680 --> 00:48:49.250 align:middle line:84%
of the temple and are dressed
in their ceremonial clothes.

00:48:49.250 --> 00:48:53.615 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:48:53.615 --> 00:49:04.770 align:middle line:90%


00:49:04.770 --> 00:49:08.190 align:middle line:84%
Within the temple itself, the
biggest and finest elephant

00:49:08.190 --> 00:49:10.620 align:middle line:90%
is being prepared.

00:49:10.620 --> 00:49:12.600 align:middle line:84%
This will be the one
which has the honor

00:49:12.600 --> 00:49:15.771 align:middle line:90%
of carrying the sacred tooth.

00:49:15.771 --> 00:49:20.741 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:49:20.741 --> 00:49:33.166 align:middle line:90%


00:49:33.166 --> 00:49:35.977 align:middle line:84%
>> The celebrations
last 10 days,

00:49:35.977 --> 00:49:38.310 align:middle line:84%
but they reached the peak of
their splendor on the night

00:49:38.310 --> 00:49:39.900 align:middle line:90%
of the full moon.

00:49:39.900 --> 00:49:47.296 align:middle line:90%


00:49:47.296 --> 00:49:49.860 align:middle line:84%
The elephant carrying
the holy palanquin

00:49:49.860 --> 00:49:52.470 align:middle line:84%
is surrounded by
priests and dignitaries,

00:49:52.470 --> 00:49:56.220 align:middle line:84%
over 1,000 dancers,
musicians, and jugglers,

00:49:56.220 --> 00:49:58.200 align:middle line:90%
and around 100 other elephants.

00:49:58.200 --> 00:50:03.160 align:middle line:90%
[FESTIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:50:03.160 --> 00:50:12.110 align:middle line:90%


00:50:12.110 --> 00:50:15.170 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the oldest
processions in the world

00:50:15.170 --> 00:50:18.650 align:middle line:84%
and is without doubt the last
where the animal, glorified

00:50:18.650 --> 00:50:23.060 align:middle line:84%
and accorded such great dignity,
is still so clearly associated

00:50:23.060 --> 00:50:24.260 align:middle line:90%
with the sacred.

00:50:24.260 --> 00:50:26.660 align:middle line:90%
[FESTIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:50:26.660 --> 00:51:05.060 align:middle line:90%


00:51:05.060 --> 00:51:09.610 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:51:09.610 --> 00:52:04.000 align:middle line:90%